---

Create a production-ready Microsoft Fabric Analytics web app named Minecraft Warehouse Operations Copilot using React 19 + TypeScript + Vite + Rayfin + Fabric App Data packages.

Goal:
Replicate my existing app behavior and structure for a warehouse operations digital twin dashboard backed by a Fabric semantic model.


Required semantic model queries:
- EVALUATE gold_currentinventory
- EVALUATE gold_heatmap
- EVALUATE gold_hourlymetrics
- EVALUATE gold_locationactivity
- EVALUATE gold_robotmovement

Core UI and behavior to implement:
- Dashboard title and warehouse operations context
- Theme toggle (light/dark)
- KPI cards:
  - Throughput (from total_events in hourly metrics)
  - Robot moves
  - Stock placed
  - Stock picked
  - Current total stock
  - Low-stock alert count (threshold 20)
- Warehouse digital twin style grid/map with zones such as Loading_Bay, Storage_Area_A, Storage_Area_B, Packing_Station, Forbidden_Zone, Control_Office
- Activity heatmap by location
- Replay/timeline controls for heatmap playback (play/pause and frame stepping)
- Low stock panel listing locations and block type
- Zone activity breakdown (placed/picked/movements)
- Robot movement trend by hour
- Location selection/filter interactions that update detail views
- Friendly empty states and error fallback UI
- Keep app responsive for desktop and mobile

Data mapping and robustness requirements:
- Build typed row mapping helpers from semantic model result tables
- Handle column name normalization safely (case and missing fields)
- Use a consistent primitive row type and transform functions for:
  - inventory points
  - heatmap points
  - zone activity stats
  - robot hour stats
- Keep throughput sourced from total_events as the reliable metric
- Include defensive handling for partial or empty query results

Project structure requirements:
- Keep a structure similar to:
  - src/App.tsx
  - src/fabric.generated.ts
  - src/components
  - src/hooks (auth + theme + semantic model query hook)
  - src/lib (fabric client, rayfin client, data table conversion)
  - src/services (rayfin auth service)
  - src/test/setup
- Include tests for:
  - semantic model query hook behavior
  - table conversion utilities

Developer experience requirements:
- Provide npm scripts for dev, build, lint, test
- Include predev/prebuild environment generation via rayfin env for Vite
- Add clear README with setup, run, test, and Fabric portal devUri instructions
- Do not leave TODO stubs; generate complete working code

